beer_description: Hazy, golden yellow color, with a big white head. Bread, tart hints, orange, yeast and clove. Sour, with soft yeast and white-bread malts, unexpected sour, compared to the other flavors of the beer. Citraic notes with unripe orange, also an noteable fzziness, due to the dominating sourness. Lively carbonation creates a fruity, slightly spiced refreshing beer, with an unusual, well fitting sourness. Decent body, soft, pleasant mouthfeel. Has a refreshing, fruity aftertaste, with a subtle bitterness.

Pours a deep mahogany brown - opaque like a chocolate liqueur - there's plenty of foam banana and some malty sweetness rising from its thick brown head. In the mouth, there's milk chocolate, cola, some burnt toffee and, of course, more of those bananas. There's plenty to chew on in a pretty creamy mouthfeel too, all rounded off with a gently lingering roast bitterness.

Brewed under license for CUB Australia.
Born of the 1963 Nastro Azzurro beer, Peroni Leggera is an expertly brewed lager using the same unique, quality Italian ingredients. Peroni Leggera, light in colour and body and has a clean, refreshing taste, with an added bitter note to provide a balanced flavour, while its effervescent sparkle acts as a great thirst quencher.
Skrimshander is an aromatic copper coloured pale ale brewed from the finest malted barley and Kentish hops.
Brewed in the style of a Russian Imperial Stout. Strong, chocolatety and aggressively hopped with finest English hops.
A classic pale ale. This version of Bass for the North American market at 5% to comply with USA ale regulations.

Apricot Ale perfectly combines the taste and aroma of fresh apricot with the smooth finish of a traditional wheat beer. It?s refreshingly unfiltered character and fruit flavor make it an ale worth savoring.

Malts:
2-Row Pale Barley & Malted Wheat

Hops:
Nugget

Brewed using the original Henley Brakspear brewing plant, including the famous ?double-drop? fermentation system, the original Copper, and the Victorian fermenting vessels. Amber in colour with a good fruit, hop, and malt nose. The initial taste of malt and well-hopped bitterness dissolves into a bitter-sweet and fruity finish.

An ale inspired by the style of a German Maibock, brewed using our proprietary Pacman yeast, Dead Guy Ale is deep honey in color with a malty aroma, rich hearty flavor and a well balanced finish.

History: In the early 1990s Dead Guy Ale was created as a private tap sticker to celebrate the Mayan Day of the Dead (November 1st, All Souls Day) for Casa U Betcha in Portland, Oregon. The Dead Guy design proved so popular with consumers and especially Grateful Dead fans, that we made it the label for our Maierbock ale. Even though the association with the Grateful Dead band is pure coincidence, we have gratefully dedicated Dead Guy Ale to the Rogue in each of us.

The Dead Guy packaging remained unchanged for 25 years until 2017 when we updated the labels with our new design.
This wonderful Pale Ale is crafted from a complex grist of roasted malts and Sussex grown hops delivering a full flavour ale with a traditional Sussex hoppy nose to the finish.
beer_name: Iron Horse Best Bitter / Premium Ale

beer_description:
Our take on an English amber ale is packed full of flavour. Malty and nutty with floral hops, fruity Yorkshire yeast and a background caramel sweetness.

Its fiery colour inspired us to name this beer after Hellfire Gully, which is an exhilarating drop off Mt Feathertop for the more adventurous backcountry skier.

Brewed with Munich, Wheat, Xtra Special and Midnight Wheat Malt, this Dunkel Doppel Weizenbock has a rich, velvety malt body with notes of milk chocolate. Higher carbonation levels give this beer a full bodied mouth feel and a fluffy, creamy head with a banana and clove aroma.

Schell Anniversary Draft Series #6, commemorating the day August Schell Brewing was found Not Guilty of Violating the 18th Amendment of the US Constitution. The 1924 Deer Brand incorporates two important indigenous American ingredients to create a unique version of the classic German Pilsner: 6-row Barley and Flaked Maize. Early American brewers discovered that by adding a portion of Maize to the high protein 6-row Barley a more palatable and stable beer could be produced. The 1924 Deer Brand is a recreation of the full-flavored American Lager your grandparents used to enjoy before and immediately following prohibition, exhibiting moderate maltiness, the complex character of our 1860 Schell yeast and a well-defined hop bitterness and flavor
beer_name: "Not Guilty" 1924 Deer Brand (Anniversary Draft Series No.6)

beer_description: Schell's Deer Brand was developed prior to Prohibition and has been Schell's flagship beer ever since. Brewed from 70 percent barley malt, 30 percent corn, and our unique 'Schell' yeast, Deer Brand is full flavored American Lager.

Schell Anniversary Draft Series #5, featuring Hopfenmalz. It is an amalgam of our favorite beer styles: the elegant drinkablity of a Pilsner, the bready maltiness of a Vienna Lager, and the hopping of a Pale Ale. The malt backbone was created using a large amount of Vienna coupled with judicious amounts of Caramunich and Caravienne. In the kettle, we agressively hopped it with Cascade and Tettnang from the Pacific Northwest. Finally, just to ensure we used enough hops, we dry hopped it also. Hopfenmalz was fermented with one of our old world lager yeasts at a higher temperature to add some flavor complexities. Finally, we aged it for six weeks to provide the crispness that is only found in a lager. Prost!

The Stag Series draws upon our 150 years of brewing knowledge at the August Schell Brewery to create a collection of innovative, limited edition beers. The first release is our Schmaltz?s Alt beer that has been aged in red wine barrels.
beer_name: Schell's Stag Series #1 Barrel Aged Schmaltz's Alt

beer_description: Draft/Cask and bottles were finished production in March 2014.
Kriek de Ranke is an unsweetened  cherry beer of mixed fermentation. It arises from a blend of old Flemish ale, lambic and 25 kilos of sour cherries/Hl.

beer_description:
A premium lager beer brewed from the finest ingredients, Singha is a full-bodied 100% barley malt beer that is distinctively rich in taste with strong hop characters. Brewed with three hops: Saaz, Perle and Hallertau. 

Editor?s Note: Recipe scaled down from 6% to 5% in 2007.
Brewed by Brouwerij Huyghe for Marks & Spencers stores UK.
Pale Ale, Maris Otter, Carapils, and Carastan malts. Cascade and Centennial hops. Clean and crisp with loads of floral and tropical fruit aromas and flavors.

Flavor grenade of American hops! With pronounced hop flavor and aroma this IPA is deliciously citrusy from tons of Cascade, Centennial, Simcoe and Amarillo hops. Full flavored, hoppy, well balanced American IPA.

Appearance
Ruby red in colour with a creamy, warm-white head.

Flavour 
Fruity aroma. A soft, full taste that develops into a lightly sweet, hoppy aftertaste.
beer_name: Charles Quint Rouge Rubis / Keizer Karel Robijn Rood

beer_description: Notre bi?re de soif par excellence, notre Pale Ale Am?ricaine, houblonn?e avec les vari?t?s Centennial, Amarillo et Cascade, offre un bouquet irr?sistible, floral et citronn?. Blonde, s?che, d?salt?rante et g?n?reusement houblonn?e!

Minerva Imperial Stout, our pride craft beer is a full bodied, dark color, aroma and flavor of cocoa and coffee, sweet stout style Ale type fermentation. The friendly and round flavor Minerva Imperial Stout marries perfectly with sweet flavors like chocolate truffles or the duck confit with light garlic mayonnaise, so it is excellent for red meats in general.

Black Metal Imperial Stout, a.k.a. Suds of Northern Darkness, a.k.a. Iron Sword, a.k.a. El Martillo del Muerte. Black Metal is a cruel and punishing beer fermented by the sheer force of its awesome will. We are pretty sure that Kreator wrote the song ?Impossible Brutality? about this beer while drinking it during their Extreme Aggression Tour.

An authentic German-style golden ale. Lower mash and fermentation temperatures, a percentage of wheat malt in the grain bill and German Hallertau hops all contribute to the refreshing flavor of this light beer.

Minerva Vienna is a bottom-fermented beer and red amber, has a faint nutty aroma and clean caramel. When you taste it and savor its distinctive soft sweetness from malt aroma. The termination is durable and mouthfeel is maltose. It is recommended to serve this beer to 6 or 8 degrees. To avail develop less foam cooler and warmer less consistent foam. Serve with sweet and sour dishes as marinated and Minerva Vienna beer refreshes the feelings generated by such dishes, also enhances the flavor of fish and vegetables.

Colonial Minerva is a bright golden colored beer with malty flavor low style and touches of citrus type fermentation Kolsch Ale, made with designation of origin in the German city Cologne. To achieve the great body that this beer boasts, is incorporated into the mixture of wheat malt and extends the dwell time after fermentation. It is recommended to serve this beer in glasses Strange (long thin glasses 20 cl) at temperatures around 10 C. Traditionally it is customary to accompany German dishes like Halve Hahn (rye bread with butter and Dutch cheese) or meats such as Blootwoosch (blood sausage).

beer_description: Brewed with all the TLC a hop-head has to offer, this bold ale tantalizes the taste buds of the serious hop lover with its pronounced bitterness and citrusy finish. Generous amounts of Cascade and Warrior hops added at the end of the kettle boil and dry-hopped in the fermenter contribute a fresh, crisp hop flavor and aroma.
Medium in body and unique in its flavor complexity. We use a combination caramel, victory, and chocolate malts to give this tasty brew a toasted, nutty flavor.
Medium in body and unique in its flavor complexity. We use a combination caramel, victory, and chocolate malts to give this tasty brew a toasted, nutty flavor.

Our Winter Wonder is brewed in the German lager style known as Schwarzbier. This beer originated as a warm fermented-style ale in central Germany before cold fermenting lager yeasts were introduced. This malty winter seasonal, though dark in color, is relatively light bodied and has a dry and refreshing finish. A careful combination of the world's finest caramel, pale and black malts give Winter Wonder its delicious roasted flavors and aromas, reminiscent of chocolate, coffee and dried fruit.

An authentic Bavarian-style ?Kristall Weizen? filtered wheat beer. The unique flavor created by the yeast has made this ale a summer favorite in the beer world.
Available April-September.

A truly spiritual ale, Evil 8? will blur the lines of what you think you know about American beer.  Brewed in the Belgian Abbey style using caramelized Biscuit malt, Goldings hops and a unique strain of brewers? yeast.
Available January-April.
This English Pale Ale is a robust, full bodies beer. It has a moderate caramel flavor with a slight chocolate essence that brings out the sharp English hop flavor.

beer_name: La Vache Folle: Centennial Double IPA

beer_description: The beer pours a brilliant gold with high carbonation and a fluffy white head. The aromas start with tropical fruit, spicy pepper, and bubble gum. The taste opens with light malt and a honey-like sweetness tempered by mint and peppery flavors. The beer transitions to herbal hoppy notes and a slightly nutty finish redolent of chestnuts. The finish is warming and dry, with a slight lingering bitterness.

beer_description: Organic. Numbered 85.000 bottles made. 4.7%

The return of an old favorite! Rover?s Waggin' Red offers a rich copper color and a wealth of malty and caramel flavors. English First Gold hops provide balance and a pleasant, lasting finish to this delicious ale.

Also sold as Cubanero Fuerte.
Bucanero brings the mystery and passion of Cuba in a golden beer, with a vigourous and robust flavour. Our ancient and secret production process combines the finest selection of hops, water and malt.

Gold Leaf Lager harkens back to the days when refreshing beers were made 100% from malted barley. Gold Leaf Lager is pale gold, light to medium bodied with subtle fresh bready notes, and a clean crisp finish.  Crisp, Clean, Bready.

This Irish Style Ale is a special blend of four types of malted barley and three varieties of hops. It is a medium-bodied ale showing off a deep reddish amber color and thick, tan bubbly head. The aroma is sweet and light followed by moderate caramel-malt flavors with a light roasty finish.

In 2006 CBSA introduced Bucanero Max, a unique premium beer that delicately balances power and finesse. At 6.5% alc./vol. Bucanero Max delivers additional strength without sacrificing the robust and vigorous flavour of Bucanero that Cubans know and love. Our secret brewing process combines the finest selection of hops, water and malted barley.
A sweet, very light, golden ale made with fresh Maine blueberries to produce a big, blueberry aroma.
brewery.brewery_name: Beer Works (Boston, Salem, Hingham, Lowell, Framingham)

beer_description:
A Baltic-style porter that blends a strong English porter with a Germanic lager approach, fairly robust ? this strong black lager has notes of chocolate and coffee with hints of caramelized sugar.  Black, Roast, Chocolate.

Our Trail Blazers stray from the beaten path into a world of robust and daring beers featuring bigger, bolder flavors for fueling your spirit of adventure.

Imagine yourself stepping out of the pilot house onto the pitching deck of a merchant ship plunging through the frigid Baltic Sea night. Squinting against the grey black horizon you spy in the distance the odd sparkle and glimmer; the far away lights of the Baltic port of Danzig are bidding you welcome. Tonight you will feast on dark rye bread and smoked pork sausage, all washed down by the famous strong black lager of the region, the Baltic-style Porter.

Meet Abby, Azrael?s darker twin. This Belgian beauty is mysteriously alluring with a sultry flavor combination of brown sugar, plum and spices in a dark burgundy hue. Abby has a deep, rich flavor, and a serious strength but like her sister, hides behind a deceptively light fruity finish. On the surface she?s the sweetest girl you?ll ever meet, but one taste you?ll be trapped in her darkly alluring web.

Gold Medal winner SIBA Award, Classic traditional stout. Complex taste with a rich and full body. Crisp with a full bouquet of spices, fruit and floral aromas. Black is a stout for the true connoisseur.

The Kilt Flasher is a hearty Scottish ale with a rich, warming complexity perfect for the onset of winter. Brown with ruby highlights, it?s an ale packed with toffee and toasted malt flavors. Much like the early Scottish settlers of the Virginia Highlands, it has a robustness that stands up to anything. Enjoy a pint today and expose yourself to great beer.  Brown, Robust, Toffee.

Named after Kelley Square right here in Worcester. This infamous traffic jam is named after WW1 veteran and local hero Cornelius Kelley. The Kolsch style is one of the lesser known German Ales. Made with 100% authentic ingredients including Kolsch yeast from our friends at Gardner Ale House. Light golden in color with light malt aroma, background fruitiness and hints of sulfur. Soft malt flavor is complimented by light fruitiness that is washed away with noble hop bitterness and a slightly dry finish. Very comparable to Pilsner or other European Lagers in most aspects.

You?ll have heard that looks can be deceiving. Well, McEwan?s Champion Ale is Exhibit A in proving that statement true. 

First impressions are of a sweet and fruity beer. But this delicate taste belies its power. As you fully get to know its intense flavours you?ll realise this is a very strong, dark and traditional ale. 

William McEwan would have been proud of it.

Dark lager with a fine yeast culture is an unpasteurized beer brewed from four types of malt, with a distinctive full taste and a fine bitterness. Its special flavour makes it unique on the Czech beer market. From Bernard?s family brewery portfolio this unfiltered beer is the most recognized in Czech and foreign degustation competitions.
brewery.brewery_name: Bernard Family Brewery/ Rodinn? pivovar Bernard a.s.

A kettle-soured cherry beer with a brown color and light body, this beer was fermented with sweet and tart cherries and then infused with toasted oak to create a complex, flavorful elixir.

We throw 75 pounds of tart Door County Cherries into each oak barrel with a rich Imperial Stout then age it for six months to create this savoy delight. Cheers!

beer_description: This smooth dark brown ale has a slightly sweet malt character that is delicately balanced by the addition of holiday spices. OG: 12.2, BUs: 25

Jim (1954-1998) is the name by which our Uncle was best known. Hill Farmstead Brewery rests upon the land that was once home to him and his four siblings. In his honor, we barrel aged our Black IPA (James) in a French Oak Pinot Noir barrel for four months and dry hopped the beer with Simcoe. Naturally carbonated and hand bottled, this is one of only 300 bottles.
Deep copper hue with a rich, caramel aroma and subtle hop perfume. Assertively bitter finish balancing the residual malt-sweetness.
American version of an India Pale Ale. Hopped extensively with Pacific Northwest Cascade, Citra and Australian summer hops.
Lightly hopped, smooth golden-straw colored. The closet we brew to your favorite domestic (not that we are aiming low!).

Quidi Vidi Honey Brown ale is created with a precise combination of Chocolate Malt and Crystal Malts, then embellished with the richness of honey and gentle hopping. A mild and wonderfully smooth ale that pours a golden brown with a hint of sweet honey scent to excite your nose.

beer_description: 'Two Brothers' as we call it at the Brewery after Skip and Walter Yahn who were the original investors in our little pub. A golden Session IPA packed with citrusy American hop flavor.

Wood Ya Honey is a wheat wine style ale brewed with generous amounts of local wild flower honey. We aged this beer in bourbon barrels for 10 months, elevating the rich caramel and honey character to luscious heights. Dripping honey comb, marzipan, and raisin come together for a decadent rich experience. Pour into your favorite snifter, let warm, sip, and allow your belly to surrender to the comforting embrace of craft.
